Coaching career
Watson served as assistant coach for Canada at the 2004 CONCACAF Men&lt;U+2019&gt;s Olympic Qualification Tournament, served as one of Canada's assistant coaches when the team finished third at the 2008 CONCACAF Men's Olympic Qualification Tournament3. Watson returned to the Charleston Battery in 2006 in a player / assistant coach role; his fifth season with the Club.4. He was later hired as an assistant coach with the San Jose Earthquakes.5
